TRADITIONAL BETTING

When betting with a bookmaker you can only bet on

the odds they offer, only having the option to back a

certain outcome. The odds set by bookies include

their margin meaning they price markets in their favor

with unfair odds. Bookmakers effectively make money

by building in a margin/over-round into their odds.

BETTING EXCHANGES

Instead of being limited to the odds set by bookies,

and only having the option to back a certain outcome,

an exchange allows users to go head-to-head against

each other by either backing or laying. It differs to

traditional sportsbooks by allowing bettors to bet

against each other, rather than a bookmaker.

