3 What is Goal Bonanza

Real game simulation

Real Madrid is a big favorite hosting Levante in the 3rd round of

Primera Division at Santiago Bernabeu. The average odds for

a home win are 1.10, with 19.00 for an away win and 10.00 for

a draw. Levante is undefeated in the last two games, they are

playing very well and tight at the back, and John believes

Levante might be able to snitch a low scoring draw in Madrid.

The crowd is backing a home win for Real Madrid and most of

the wagers go on “GOAL BONANZA” and home win game

scores. John however, wagers 5 tokens on 0:0, 1:1 and 2:2,

each and hedged his draw prediction with 15 tokens on “GOAL

BONANZA” to cover his losses in case Real Madrid trashes

Levente. On the right you can see the expected distribution of

stakes in a football game with a home team as a huge favorite.

John just made profit of $45,782.85 (Total returns – total stake).

No traditional bookmaker or betting exchange could match this.

If the game ended up with a high scoring home win, John

would get his stakes back by hedging his draw bets with 15

tokens on “GOAL BONANZA” at 2.10 to 1. Real Madrid was a

big favorite in the match and the crowd is heavily backing the

most probable outcome. The potential returns on the less

probable outcomes are exponentially growing and the crowd is

more keen to back an underdog. This behavior on the other

side increases the potential returns for backing a home win that

no traditional bookmaker of betting exchange can match.

